
Setting up MetalLB LoadBalancer with NGINX on Bare-metal Kubernetes
Prerequisites

A working Kubernetes cluster (multi-node or single-node)

kubectl installed and configured

All nodes able to communicate on the same network/subnet

Container runtime installed (e.g., containerd)

1. Verify Cluster Nodes

Check that all nodes are Ready:

kubectl get nodes -o wide

Expected output should show all your nodes in Ready status with internal IPs.

2. Install MetalLB

Apply MetalLB manifests:

kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/metallb/metallb/v0.15.3/config/manifests/metallb-native.yaml

Verify the pods:

kubectl get pods -n metallb-system -o wide

You should see:

controller running

speaker running on all nodes

⚠️ If some speaker pods are in ContainerCreating or CrashLoopBackOff, ensure all nodes can communicate via network.

3. Configure MetalLB IP Address Pool

Create a config file metallb-config.yaml:

apiVersion: metallb.io/v1beta1
kind: IPAddressPool
metadata:
  name: default-address-pool
  namespace: metallb-system
spec:
  addresses:
  - 192.168.122.240-192.168.122.250   # Adjust to your free IP range
---
apiVersion: metallb.io/v1beta1
kind: L2Advertisement
metadata:
  name: default-l2
  namespace: metallb-system
spec:
  ipAddressPools:
  - default-address-pool

Apply the configuration:

kubectl apply -f metallb-config.yaml

Verify:

kubectl get ipaddresspool -n metallb-system
kubectl get l2advertisement -n metallb-system
4. Deploy Test NGINX Pod

Create test-nginx-lb.yaml:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: test-nginx
  labels:
    app: test-nginx
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:stable
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: test-nginx-lb
spec:
  selector:
    app: test-nginx
  type: LoadBalancer
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80

Apply it:

kubectl apply -f test-nginx-lb.yaml
5. Verify Service and LoadBalancer IP

Check the LoadBalancer service:

kubectl get svc test-nginx-lb

Expected output:

NAME            TYPE           CLUSTER-IP     EXTERNAL-IP       PORT(S)        AGE
test-nginx-lb   LoadBalancer   10.98.95.219   192.168.122.240   80:31302/TCP   0s

EXTERNAL-IP should be from the MetalLB IP pool

6. Test NGINX LoadBalancer

Test locally from master node:

curl http://192.168.122.240

You should see:

<h1>Welcome to nginx!</h1>

Test from other nodes in the same network to ensure MetalLB is reachable.

7. Verify Pods

Check pods and their node distribution:

kubectl get pods -o wide

Ensure test-nginx pod is running

MetalLB speakers running on all nodes
